    <h1>David K. Winter <br> Servant Leadership<br> Awards</h1> 
   </div> 
   <div id="content"> 
    <p>The Office of Student Life is sponsoring the 15th annual David K. Winter Servant Leadership Award. All students who are returning for the 2015-2016 academic year are eligible for these awards. Ten $1,000 awards will be granted to students who have been nominated by faculty, staff, and students for clearly demonstrating Christ-like character through servant leadership. The David K Winter Selection Committee will also take into consideration nominees’ academic (minimum 3.0 GPA) and behavioral standing with the college.</p> 
    <p>Please consider nominating a student for one of these awards. Students nominated generally evidence integrity, collaboration skills, a passion for service, and empathy. Nominees are trusted and respected by their peers, reveal a servant’s heart in their roles on and off campus, and make a significant impact on the organization/group/activity. All nominations must be submitted by Friday, February 27th . </p> 
    <p><b><i>Please briefly respond to the following questions.&nbsp; </i></b></p> 
